13.03	Angana_P._Chatterji	Angana P. Chatterji	Angana P. Chatterji (born November 1966) is an anthropologist, left-wing activist and feminist historian, born and raised in Kolkata, India. She is a co-convener of the International People's Tribunal on Human Rights and Justice in Indian-administered Kashmir.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/3d/Angana_Chatterji.JPG
